<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Messrs. <persName type="from">Hopkins &amp;
                                    Hopkins</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington Loan and Trust Building</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December 15, 1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: We have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of the Department’s letter of the 14th instant, relative to the
                            seizure of the <hi rend="italic">Mashona</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Maria</hi> by her Majesty’s cruiser <hi rend="italic">Partridge</hi>, and inquiring whether our clients, Messrs. Flint,
                            Eddy &amp; Co., are American citizens.</p>
                        <p>In response we have to state that Messrs. Flint, Eddy &amp; Co. are
                            American citizens domiciled in the city of New York.</p>
                        <p>We are, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed>
                                <list>
                                    <item><hi rend="smallcaps">Hopkins &amp; Hopkins</hi>,</item>
                                    <item>Per <hi rend="smallcaps">S. G. Hopkins.</hi></item>
                                </list>
                            </signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>